  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN137.1-kilavi">talaimakaṉ <app><lem>piriyumeṉa</lem><rdg wit="#C2 #C3 #C7 #C9v #RK">piriyumeṉak karuti</rdg></app> vēṟupaṭṭa talaimakaṭkut tōḻi colliyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">What the confidante said to HER who had undergone changes [at the thought] 
            that HE would part [from her].</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="AN137.1">
              <l>āṟucel vampalarc cēṟukiḷait tuṇṭa</l>
              <l>ciṟupal kēṇip piṭiyaṭi nacaiik</l>
              <l>kaḷiṟutoṭūuk kaṭakkuṅ kāṉyāṟ ṟattañ</l>
              <l>ceṉṟucēr pollā rāyiṉu niṉakkē</l>
              <l>veṉṟeṟi muraciṉ viṟaṟpōrc cōḻa</l>
              <l>riṉkaṭuṅ kaḷḷi ṉuṟantai yāṅkaṇ</l>
              <l>varupuṉa ṉeritaru mirukaraip pēryāṟ</l>
              <l>ṟuruva veṇmaṇaṉ murukunāṟu taṇpoḻiṟ</l>
              <l>paṅkuṉi muyakkaṅ kaḻinta va<supplied>ḻi</supplied>nā<supplied>ḷ</supplied></l>
              <l>vīyilai yamaṉṟa marampayi liṟumpiṟ</l>
              <l>ṟīyi laṭuppi ṉaraṅkam pōla</l>
              <l>perumpāḻ koṇṭaṉṟu nutalē tō<supplied>ḷu</supplied>n</l>
              <l>tō<supplied>ḷā</supplied> muttiṟ ṟeṇkaṭaṟ porunaṉ</l>
              <l>ṟiṇṭērc ceḻiyaṉ poruppil kavāa</l>
              <l>ṉalleḻi ṉeṭuvēy puraiyun</l>
              <l>tolkaviṉ ṟolaintaṉa nōkō yāṉē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l>Even though he did not agree to join in going (4)</l>
                <l>on the road by the forest river, which the elephant bull touches [and] crosses, (3)</l>
                <l>longing for the feet of [his] females [when seeing] the many little wells (2)</l>
                <l>from which travellers that go the way drink after digging up the mud, (1)</l>
                <l>like (11d)</l>
                <l>in that place, Uṟantai, with the sweet hot toddy</l>
                <l>of the Cōḻa with victorious battles, [his] drum beaten in victory, (5f.)</l>
                <l>in cool groves fragrant with perfume in the shapely white sand</l>
                <l>from the big river with two shores that are crushed by the coming flood, (7f.)</l>
                <l>in the successive days that passed in the embrace of Phalguni, (9)</l>
                <l>in the rustling thicket of trees overgrown with flowers [and] leaves, (10)</l>
                <l rend="indent4">the festival place with fireless ovens, (11a-c)</l>
                <l>great ruin has overtaken your forehead, and [your] shoulders, (12)</l>
                <l>[their] old beauty,(16a)</l>
                <l>that resembles the good, graceful, tall bamboo</l>
                <l>on the mountain slope of Ceḻiyaṉ with a firm chariot,</l>
                <l>fighter from the cool sea with unperforated pearls, (13-15)</l>
                <l rend="indent6">is lost. Ah, I ache. (16b-d)</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>
